95
00:10:22,622 --> 00:10:23,748
Five days to be exact.

96
00:10:24,415 --> 00:10:27,293
She's been out of it
since she came back from her leave.

97
00:10:27,961 --> 00:10:29,587
Did something happen?

98
00:10:32,799 --> 00:10:34,467
What's wrong with me?

99
00:10:47,689 --> 00:10:49,607
This isn't right.

100
00:10:57,365 --> 00:10:58,449
SOL-I

101
00:11:03,580 --> 00:11:04,872
-Yes?
-What?

102
00:11:04,956 --> 00:11:07,083
It's not like you to answer right away.

103
00:11:07,166 --> 00:11:08,459
What's up?

104
00:11:08,543 --> 00:11:10,545
Come over after work.

105
00:11:10,628 --> 00:11:11,754
I have a new dish.

106
00:11:11,838 --> 00:11:13,673
Next time. I'm busy.

107
00:11:13,756 --> 00:11:16,801
Again? But your last project just ended.

108
00:11:16,884 --> 00:11:18,344
I need to test out my dish.

109
00:11:18,428 --> 00:11:20,096
Call someone else.

110
00:11:23,433 --> 00:11:26,311
Why don't you try calling Gu Eun-ho?

111
00:11:26,936 --> 00:11:28,104
He's trying it right now.

112
00:11:28,730 --> 00:11:31,941
But he says everything tastes bad.
I can't trust him.

113
00:11:32,525 --> 00:11:33,401
What?

114
00:11:34,027 --> 00:11:35,987
Why's he over there? Isn't he working?

115
00:11:36,070 --> 00:11:36,988
Is he not busy?

116
00:11:37,655 --> 00:11:40,199
-Hey, aren't you busy?
-No.

117
00:11:40,283 --> 00:11:42,493
Why are you always free?
Don't you have work?

118
00:11:45,830 --> 00:11:47,957
It seems like he's unemployed.

119
00:11:48,041 --> 00:11:49,876
He's resting since Ung's taking a break.

120
00:11:50,585 --> 00:11:51,502
He's taking a break?

121
00:11:51,586 --> 00:11:53,963
Anyway, come over after you get off work.

122
00:12:00,219 --> 00:12:03,014
What is Ung thinking?

123
00:13:12,792 --> 00:13:14,460
How long have I been like this?

124
00:13:33,438 --> 00:13:34,522
Mom.

125
00:13:54,083 --> 00:13:55,084
Mom!

126
00:13:55,835 --> 00:13:57,044
You're up.

127
00:13:57,128 --> 00:13:59,380
Come here.
Let me see if your fever's down.

128
00:14:06,345 --> 00:14:08,473
Your fever's all gone.

129
00:14:09,056 --> 00:14:12,560
You get a bad fever when you catch a cold.

130
00:14:13,478 --> 00:14:16,439
Have you been taking the medicine
I sent you last time?

131
00:14:16,522 --> 00:14:18,274
-Yes.
-Really?

132
00:14:18,357 --> 00:14:20,193
You only took some and stopped, right?

133
00:14:20,276 --> 00:14:23,362
I heard you got drenched
in the rain during the trip.

134
00:14:24,238 --> 00:14:27,533
I should rip Eun-ho's mouth out.

135
00:14:34,749 --> 00:14:36,250
But what were you doing here?

136
00:14:36,334 --> 00:14:39,712
I think this is the first time
seeing your drawings

137
00:14:39,796 --> 00:14:41,005
up close like this.

138
00:14:42,757 --> 00:14:45,259
You left early when I drew at that event.

139
00:14:49,555 --> 00:14:53,476
When did my son grow up so much?

140
00:14:55,269 --> 00:14:56,437
What?

141
00:14:57,605 --> 00:15:00,024
I've been a grown man for quite a while.

142
00:15:04,403 --> 00:15:06,280
Why did you grow up all alone?

143
00:15:09,158 --> 00:15:11,536
It must have been difficult for you.

144
00:15:13,329 --> 00:15:16,415
Don't try to carry
all the burden yourself.

145
00:15:16,499 --> 00:15:17,583
You don't have to.

146
00:15:20,127 --> 00:15:23,381
I guess me and Dad
are still quite lacking

147
00:15:23,464 --> 00:15:25,466
for you to depend on us.

148
00:15:26,509 --> 00:15:28,719
It's not that, so don't worry.

149
00:15:29,345 --> 00:15:31,806
I'm just more comfortable alone.

150
00:15:32,807 --> 00:15:35,518
Ung, but still…

151
00:15:35,601 --> 00:15:38,437
Mom, it's okay.
I like the way things are right now.

152
00:15:41,899 --> 00:15:44,068
It's okay to be alone from the start.

153
00:15:44,902 --> 00:15:46,070
You'd be used to it.

154
00:15:47,780 --> 00:15:49,740
But being alone after being with someone

155
00:15:51,200 --> 00:15:53,286
isn't something

156
00:16:05,673 --> 00:16:08,050
We just had instant noodles
for lunch the first day.

157
00:16:08,134 --> 00:16:11,137
And we grilled meat
and made stew for dinner.

158
00:16:11,220 --> 00:16:13,222
One of them was a really good cook.

159
00:16:13,889 --> 00:16:15,266
And then the next day…

160
00:16:16,767 --> 00:16:18,769
What did we have again?

161
00:16:20,062 --> 00:16:22,982
Right, the cast slept in,
so the rest of us ate out.

162
00:16:23,065 --> 00:16:24,150
And then for lunch--

163
00:16:24,233 --> 00:16:26,861
Hey, I wasn't asking what you ate there.

164
00:16:27,987 --> 00:16:28,988
I see.

165
00:16:30,031 --> 00:16:33,117
Ji-ung filmed Ms. Kook on the first day,

166
00:16:33,200 --> 00:16:35,286
and Chae-ran filmed Mr. Choi.

167
00:16:35,369 --> 00:16:37,413
I stayed back and set up the lights.

168
00:16:37,496 --> 00:16:39,624
And we filmed at the house in the evening.

169
00:16:39,707 --> 00:16:41,167
-And then--
-No, not that.

170
00:16:41,250 --> 00:16:44,295
Didn't anything interesting happen?

171
00:16:45,796 --> 00:16:48,549
Right. The casts' friends were really fun.

172
00:16:48,633 --> 00:16:51,510
They showed me around the village.

173
00:16:53,054 --> 00:16:55,097
Hey. Eat up.

174
00:16:55,181 --> 00:16:56,390
Drink up.

175
00:16:56,474 --> 00:16:57,642
Just shut up and drink.

176
00:16:59,060 --> 00:17:00,353
Jeez.

177
00:17:04,231 --> 00:17:06,317
Oh, right.

178
00:17:06,901 --> 00:17:08,653
There was heavy rain all of a sudden

179
00:17:08,736 --> 00:17:11,197
so we had to stop filming for a whole day.

180
00:17:11,864 --> 00:17:12,698
And?

181
00:17:12,782 --> 00:17:16,243
Chae-ran was with Ms. Kook,
but she came back alone.

182
00:17:17,244 --> 00:17:20,206
And then Ji-ung arrived
with Ms. Kook a while later.

183
00:17:20,873 --> 00:17:25,670
And Mr. Choi was gone for a long time
then came back all drenched.

184
00:17:26,796 --> 00:17:28,089
Is that so?

185
00:17:28,172 --> 00:17:30,216
So what happened?

186
00:17:30,299 --> 00:17:31,676
We canceled the shoot.

187
00:17:32,426 --> 00:17:34,261
We were going to film more the next day,

188
00:17:34,345 --> 00:17:37,139
but we couldn't because the cast
went back to Seoul in the morning.

189
00:17:37,223 --> 00:17:39,100
I see…

190
00:17:39,892 --> 00:17:41,852
But why didn't you tell me earlier?

191
00:17:41,936 --> 00:17:44,605
You should have told me
when I asked if anything happened!

192
00:17:46,649 --> 00:17:48,943
But why did the cast leave so early?

193
00:17:49,735 --> 00:17:52,655
Well, it seemed like urgent business.

194
00:17:53,364 --> 00:17:56,909
But it did seem like
something was going on.

195
00:17:57,868 --> 00:18:00,037
It felt like the cast might have fought…

196
00:18:00,121 --> 00:18:03,249
No, it felt different than a fight.

197
00:18:03,958 --> 00:18:05,584
But what's even more strange

198
00:18:05,668 --> 00:18:08,379
is that Ji-ung and Chae-ran
were acting weird too.

199
00:18:08,462 --> 00:18:09,922
They were quiet.

200
00:18:10,005 --> 00:18:11,757
-Why?
-Well…

201
00:18:12,425 --> 00:18:14,635
I'm not sure why.

202
00:18:14,719 --> 00:18:18,431
But the two of them went out to talk
that night for a long time.

203
00:18:19,140 --> 00:18:21,058
Just the two of them?

204
00:18:22,810 --> 00:18:25,771
Really? Is that so?

205
00:18:45,833 --> 00:18:47,752
Ji-ung, I ordered dinner.

206
00:18:48,461 --> 00:18:49,628
Come and have some later.

207
00:19:01,432 --> 00:19:02,558
Did you get off work?

208
00:19:05,478 --> 00:19:06,979
Did you have dinner yet?

209
00:19:13,319 --> 00:19:14,403
Did you get a good…

210
00:19:18,532 --> 00:19:20,117
I want to make it seem like

211
00:19:21,494 --> 00:19:23,287
nothing's happened between us, but…

212
00:19:39,512 --> 00:19:41,889
KIM JI-UNG

213
00:19:56,654 --> 00:19:58,614
Where are you? Give me the address.

214
00:19:58,697 --> 00:20:00,116
Are you coming for me?

215
00:20:00,199 --> 00:20:02,701
I can find you easily. Delete the video.

216
00:20:03,285 --> 00:20:04,370
I'm the producer.

217
00:20:04,453 --> 00:20:07,039
Not if you end up dead. Delete it.

218
00:20:07,957 --> 00:20:09,834
You make that face all the time anyway.

219
00:20:09,917 --> 00:20:11,710
That's the best I can get out of you.

220
00:20:12,628 --> 00:20:14,505
It's the producer that's the problem.

221
00:20:17,299 --> 00:20:19,885
LEEZAKAYA

222
00:20:20,678 --> 00:20:22,930
Fine, I'll delete it.

223
00:20:23,013 --> 00:20:24,056
Did you have dinner?

224
00:20:51,125 --> 00:20:52,167
WITH UNG

225
00:20:52,793 --> 00:20:54,712
-You're back.
-Hey.

226
00:20:54,795 --> 00:20:56,547
How is he? Is his fever down?

227
00:20:56,630 --> 00:20:57,631
Yes.

228
00:20:58,382 --> 00:21:01,510
His fever's down,
and I gave him some food.

229
00:21:06,307 --> 00:21:08,350
-But why do you look so down?
-What?

230
00:21:08,434 --> 00:21:11,562
-Is he not feeling well?
-It's not that.

231
00:21:11,645 --> 00:21:14,148
I looked around his studio,

232
00:21:14,231 --> 00:21:16,233
and it seemed
he still has trouble sleeping.

233
00:21:16,317 --> 00:21:18,444
He has a lot more pills now.

234
00:21:19,361 --> 00:21:21,739
He must be spending all his time there.

235
00:21:22,239 --> 00:21:25,284
When I looked around,

236
00:21:25,367 --> 00:21:27,453
it seemed so lonely there.

237
00:21:28,120 --> 00:21:29,788
-Is that so?
-Yes.

238
00:21:31,415 --> 00:21:35,336
Do you think he will be okay like this?

239
00:21:38,088 --> 00:21:40,174
Ung isn't that weak.

240
00:21:40,257 --> 00:21:42,384
He'll be all right.

241
00:21:53,771 --> 00:21:55,147
UNG'S DRAWINGS ORGANIZED BY EUN-HO

242
00:22:42,194 --> 00:22:43,696
DRAWINGS FROM UNG'S DARK TIMES

243
00:22:45,864 --> 00:22:48,409
I like that you're an amazing artist

244
00:22:48,492 --> 00:22:51,161
but I hope you never experience

245
00:23:32,119 --> 00:23:34,747
-Did you sleep with him?
-Are you crazy?

246
00:23:35,748 --> 00:23:38,584
So that means you're ruining my new dish

247
00:23:38,667 --> 00:23:41,253
over something as trivial as a kiss?

248
00:23:41,336 --> 00:23:42,337
"Trivial"?

249
00:23:42,421 --> 00:23:45,257
Is that why you two ran away the next day?

250
00:23:45,966 --> 00:23:47,926
That's so boring!

251
00:23:48,010 --> 00:23:49,595
Isn't there anything interesting?

252
00:23:52,056 --> 00:23:55,434
Honestly, it's more surprising
that nothing has happened until now.

253
00:23:56,018 --> 00:23:57,686
If I were with my ex,

254
00:23:57,770 --> 00:24:00,522
I'd be overwhelmed with regret

255
00:24:00,606 --> 00:24:02,024
and become all sentimental.

256
00:24:02,107 --> 00:24:04,193
I'd get wasted and jump at him.

257
00:24:04,276 --> 00:24:08,572
I really must be crazy
to come here and tell you all this.

258
00:24:08,655 --> 00:24:10,741
Hey, you're adults.

259
00:24:10,824 --> 00:24:12,826
Plus, you two used to date.

260
00:24:12,910 --> 00:24:16,330
Things like that can happen
when the mood is right.

261
00:24:16,413 --> 00:24:18,290
Everyone does that. What's the problem?

262
00:24:18,373 --> 00:24:20,167
Not everyone is like you.

263
00:24:20,250 --> 00:24:22,044
Not everyone is like you, either.

264
00:24:24,296 --> 00:24:28,634
Just say, "Oh, it was a mistake"
and forget about it.

265
00:24:28,717 --> 00:24:30,427
It's not that simple.

266
00:24:31,053 --> 00:24:34,348
You always seem to complicate things.

267
00:24:35,182 --> 00:24:39,645
Why are you sulking? What's the problem?

268
00:24:39,728 --> 00:24:41,980
He hasn't called me since then

